import java.util.*;
class Solution {
    public int romanToInt(String s) {
       Map<Character,Integer>map=Map.of('I',1,'V',5,'X',10,'L',50,'C',100,'D',500,'M',1000);
       int r=0;
       for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
        int cu=map.get(s.charAt(i));
        int n=(i+1<s.length())?map.get(s.charAt(i+1)):0;
        if(cu<n){
            r-=cu;
        }
        else{
            r+=cu;
        }
       }
       return r;
    }
}

how the code works:
first, we go thru the first 2 elements of the given roman number. 
we check if they are in ascending order(to add numbers) or descending order(to subract numbers),
so that with respect to it we can convert in into the required number.
Then we use the same process with the next two varialbes(roman numbers).
After the last roman number, we can print the required number.
